{
  "id": "PLACE_the_ironstraked_passage",
  "label": "The Iron-Straked Passage",
  "description": "A narrow internal corridor cut along The Oathcutter’s reinforced spine, its bulkheads clad in tar-black planking and banded with iron straps to resist ramming shock. Pitch-sealed seams and riveted plates bead with brine, and the air carries the persistent stink of tar, damp hemp, and bilge-salt. Registry marks and stamped jurisdiction plaques are set at intervals beside each hatch, turning simple transit into an ordered chain of controlled access. A line of salt-caked warding nails runs waist-high along the length, their standard hazard sigils re-inked directly into the wood.",
